    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>Our application uses Google services, including Gmail and Google Sheets, for the purpose of managing customer data, marketing communications, and customer information. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring compliance with GDPR regulations.</p>

    <h2>1. Data Collection and Processing</h2>
    <p>We collect and process personal data through Gmail and Google Sheets for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Customer Communication</strong>: We use Gmail to send transactional emails and notifications related to your account, purchases, or any services you subscribe to.</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing Purposes</strong>: With your explicit consent, we may use your email address to send marketing materials, promotions, or updates about our products and services.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Management</strong>: Google Sheets is used for securely storing and managing customer data, ensuring accurate records for our services.</li>
        <li><strong>Customer Support</strong>: To provide customer support efficiently, we may store customer inquiries and interaction history within Google Sheets.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We use secure systems and encryption protocols provided by Google to ensure your data is protected. Access to data stored in Google Sheets and Gmail is restricted to authorized personnel only.</p>

    <h2>3. Legal Basis for Data Processing</h2>
    <p>We process your personal data based on the following legal grounds under GDPR:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Contractual Necessity</strong>: To fulfill the services you have requested from us.</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate Interest</strong>: For the maintenance and improvement of our services.</li>
        <li><strong>Consent</strong>: For marketing communications and other optional data processing activities.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain your personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this policy. You have the right to request deletion of your data at any time by contacting us.</p>

    <h2>5. User Rights under GDPR</h2>
    <p>Under GDPR, you have the following rights regarding your data:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>The right to access your personal data.</li>
        <li>The right to rectify any incorrect or incomplete information.</li>
        <li>The right to request the deletion of your data (right to be forgotten).</li>
        <li>The right to object to or restrict processing of your data.</li>
        <li>The right to data portability.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Contact Information</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions or concerns about our privacy practices or wish to exercise your rights, please contact us at: pingplaytm@gmail.com</p>

    <h2>7. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. The latest version will always be available at this link.</p>

